Get labels from the API, not .runner — I steered you wrong on that earlier; labels aren't reliably stored in that file. This is authoritative:

powershell
gh api /enterprises/YOUR-ENTERPRISE/actions/runners `
  --jq '.runners[] | {id, name, status, busy, group: .runner_group_id, labels: [.labels[] | select(.type=="custom") | .name]}'

Save that output. type=="custom" filters out self-hosted, Windows, X64, which are applied automatically and must not be passed to --labels.

