Three things worth knowing:

--replace lets you reuse the name if the server still has the old registration — without it you'd get a name conflict.

The password appears briefly in the config.cmd process command line, visible to anyone who can read Win32_Process on that box. If that's a concern, drop --unattended and --windowslogonpassword and let it prompt interactively instead.

Don't add --disableupdate. Given the version enforcement you're already contending with, you want auto-update on.
